{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and line a large baking tray with baking paper.","Place orange peel and 40 g sugar in mixing bowl then grind <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add remaining 60 g sugar and egg then mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add baking powder, flour, apricots, almonds and pistachio nuts then mix <nobr>30 sec\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Finish mixing by hand with spatula if necessary.","Flour prepared baking tray then tip sticky dough onto it. Gently bring together into a log shape (approx. 30 cm x 6 cm) - see tip.","Brush with milk then bake for 20 minutes (180°C). Remove from oven and allow to cool for 5 minutes.","Transfer log to a chopping board then use a serrated bread knife to cut in slices on the diagonal (1.5 cm wide). Arrange slices, flat side down, on baking tray then bake for 5 minutes (180°C) on each side. Transfer biscuits to a wire rack and allow to cool.","Serve, or store in an airtight container until needed."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 orange, thin peelings of skin only","100 g caster sugar","1 large egg","½ tsp baking powder","130 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","60 g dried apricots, quartered","60 g almonds","60 g pistachio nuts, unsalted, shelled","1 Tbsp milk, for brushing"]}],"id":"r133356","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-7FJ-75NxpYw\/XZWqo4w0UuI\/AAAAAAAAfbA\/TEzlzohURiI5-pxZifOQ1TqGVUdasKVqgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_RQLRcXptEIXpX5CM.png","title":"Apricot, Almond and Pistachio Biscotti","publishedAt":"2017-11-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3 g","fat":"4.3 g","uom":"per 0 piece","carbohydrates":"15.5 g","calories":"472 kJ \/ 113 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray and paper, pastry brush, tongs, chopping board, wire rack, bread knife, oven","hintsAndTricks":["If the dough is very sticky, use wet hands to help shape it.","Biscotti will keep for up to 1 month if stored in an airtight container."],"basicInf